# Telco Customer Churn Prediction

## Overview

This project predicts whether a telecom customer is likely to churn using Machine Learning. It also includes an interactive Streamlit web application for data exploration (EDA), model comparison, and customer churn prediction.

## Features

* Data preprocessing and feature engineering
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Interactive visualizations
* Customer churn prediction
* Comparison of multiple Machine Learning models
* User-friendly Streamlit interface

## Machine Learning Models

The project uses three trained models:

* Logistic Regression
* Random Forest
* XGBoost

## Project Structure

```text
├── app.py                  # Streamlit application
├── Telco_Churn.ipynb       # Jupyter notebook (EDA, preprocessing, model training)
├── logistic_model.pkl
├── random_forest_model.pkl
├── xgboost_model.pkl
├── scaler.pkl
├── encoder.pkl
└── README.md
```

> File names may vary depending on your saved models.

## Dataset

The project uses the **Telco Customer Churn** dataset containing customer demographics, services, billing information, and churn status.

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Scikit-learn
* XGBoost
* Streamlit

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd <repository-folder>
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Run the Streamlit application:

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

## Input Features

The application accepts customer information such as:

* Gender
* Senior Citizen
* Partner
* Dependents
* Tenure
* Phone Service
* Internet Service
* Contract Type
* Payment Method
* Monthly Charges
* Total Charges
* and other service-related features.

Users enter the original customer information; all preprocessing and encoding are handled automatically by the application.

## Project Workflow

1. Data Cleaning
2. Feature Engineering
3. Data Preprocessing
4. Model Training
5. Model Evaluation
6. Streamlit Dashboard
7. Customer Churn Prediction

## Future Improvements

* Hyperparameter tuning
* Additional visualization options
